This is als mini-FAQ.
---------------------

Q: How can I exit from command line without removing all it content. Is there
   a hot-key except ENTER?
A: You can place this lines in /etc/inputrc or ~/.inputrc:
	set meta-flag on
	set convert-meta off
	set input-meta on
	set output-meta on
	"\C-x": "\C-e\C-u\C-d"
   Restart als and now you can leave command line by pressing Ctrl+x.
   For more information please see man readline.

Q: I can't see some files. For example .profile or .bashrc.
A: Press Ctrl+H or see .alsrc for "hidden" keyword.
